  "title": "Conductors - connecting spheres with equal sigma",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two positively-charged conducting spheres, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, have radii <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub A\"><math alttext=\"r sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub B\"><math alttext=\"r sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math></span></span>, respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub B is greater than r sub A\"><math alttext=\"r sub B is greater than r sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub></math></span></span>. The two spheres initially have the same uniform surface charge <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">density</span> and are located far apart so that their electric fields do not affect one another. Which of the following describes what will happen when a thin conducting wire is connected to both spheres and best explains why?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
